50|$|As an {{informal}} fallacy, the <b>red</b> <b>herring</b> {{falls into a}} broad class of relevance fallacies. Unlike the straw man, which is premised on a distortion of the other party's position, the <b>red</b> <b>herring</b> is a seemingly plausible, though ultimately irrelevant, diversionary tactic. According to the Oxford English Dictionary, a <b>red</b> <b>herring</b> may be intentional, or unintentional; {{it does not necessarily}} mean a conscious intent to mislead.|$|R
